My mother spoke Spanish to me when I was young, that is why I put 0 as the age I started learning Spanish, but I did not start studying Spanish until I was in middle school at 11. Because my mother spoke to me in Spanish when I was young there are some phrases and words in Spanish that I know instinctively without having to translate in my head, there are even some words that I learned in Spanish first and did not learn the English counterpart for until much later in life, which is why I sometimes would forget the English word for something even though I could not hold a conversation in Spanish. It has been really interesting to learn Spanish with this background, because there are a few grammar rules in Spanish that I know because they just "sound right" to me from listening to my family speak and then in class I get to learn why those specific grammar rules exist and how they work.
I work as a bilingual nutrition educator and regularly use Spanish in my professional and personal interactions
